rnal source  Eligible for Operating Reserve only \nwithin Eastern Interconnect\n Not subject to Energy dispatch  ...    TIED\n11\n• COM\nGENERATION\n Individual (single) generation unit \nconsisting of physically connected generator(s), reactor(s), boiler(s), \ncombustion turbine(s) or other prime \nmover(s) operated together to produce electric power\n Capable of following dispatch\nGENERATING \nUNIT\nPLANT GEN PLT  Aggregated Resource consisting of \nmultiple generating units at the same \nplant\n Capable of following dispatch\n12  ...    combustion turbine and a portion of \nsteam turbine\n4. Register as MCR (see details on the \nright)\nMULTI-CONFIGURATION  ...     Resources type will not be CC when\nMCR option is selected\n13\nGENERATION\nJOINTLY OWNED \nUNIT JOU  GENs with more than one owner may \nbe registered as JOU or CIR\n May model JOU shares using the  ...    *NOTE: CIR is not a Resource type. Resources associated with a CIR configuration will be registered as a \"GEN\" and have a flag of \"Y\" under the \"CIR Reference\" column in the Appendix B \n\"Resources\" tab. \n14\nMARKET STORAGE RESOURCE  Used to model Electric Storage Resources \n(ESRs) as defined by FERC\n Modeled as a GEN with negative or positive output\n Eligible for Energy, Operating Reserves, \nincluding Ramp Capability products  Must be capable of providing 0.1 MW for at \nleast one (1) hour\nMARKET STORAGE \nRESOURCE* MSR *NOTE: (An ENERGY STORAGE RESOURCE\nmay also register under one of the \nGENERATION types)\n15\n• COM VARIABLE ENERGY RESOURCES\n Capable of being incrementally \ndispatched\n Eligible for Energy, Reg-Down and  ...     Special commitment and dispatch \nrules apply to RUC and RTBM\nDISPATCHABLE \nVARIABLE ENERGY\nNON-DISPATCHABLE VARIABLE ENERGY\nDVER NDVER\n Must be a Qualifying Facility exercising their rights \nunder PURPA "
